Ken Narasaki https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Narasaki 0 Ken Narasaki (born April 4, 1958 in Seattle, Washington) is a Yonsei (fourth-generation Japanese American) playwright and actor. He is the former Literary Manager at East West Players theatre company in Los Angeles. He is the twin brother of civil rights leader Karen Narasaki.
